# Portfolio Website - Aman Kumar

Welcome to my personal portfolio website! This project showcases my skills, experience, and projects in web development and design.

## 🚀 Live Demo
Check out the live version of my portfolio: [Portfolio Website](https://aman-kumar778.github.io/Portfolio-website-Aman/)

## 📌 Features
- **Responsive Design**: Ensures optimal viewing on various devices.
- **Dynamic Hero Section**: Engaging visuals with interactive elements.
- **Service Offerings**: Detailed overview of services including Front-End Development, Back-End Development, Blockchain Development, and Video Editing.
- **Project Showcase**: In-depth descriptions of recent projects with visuals and links.
- **About Me Section**: Insights into my background, skills, and experiences.
- **Contact Information**: Easy access to reach out via email or phone.

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- **Front-End**: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

## 📂 Project Structure
```
Portfolio-website-Aman/
│── index.html         # Main HTML file
│── css/               # Stylesheets
│── js/                # JavaScript files
│── assets/            # Images and media
│── README.md
```

## 🎨 UI & Design
The website follows a modern, clean design with responsive elements. It adapts to different screen sizes for an optimal experience on all devices.

## 📂 Featured Projects
### 1. **E-Commerce Website**
- Built using React.js, Strapi, and Stripe.
- Features product listings, search functionality, and checkout system.
- Fully responsive and user-friendly.


## 🖥️ Setup & Installation
To run this project locally, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Aman-Kumar778/Portfolio-website-Aman.git
   ```
2. Navigate to the project folder:
   ```bash
   cd Portfolio-website-Aman
   ```
3. Open `index.html` in your browser.

